All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ActiveAirportWaypoint
This class is a Waypoint on the Map which represents an active Airport (in red).
Airport
The Airport class represents the different airports which are imported (in this case, France's airports).
AirportSet
The AirportSet class is a container for the Airport class.
AirportWaypoint
This class is the MapWaypoint which is used to represent Airports on the Map.
App
This class loads the application.
Automation
Automates every step of the Coloring Challenge where we have to import 20 graphs, color them and store the results.
ColoringAlgorithms
Enum storing constants linked to algorithms, it defines for each algorithm an ID : - to identify it or index it a String : - for its toString method a Method (can be null) : - the method that implements the algorithm
ColoringDSATUR
Class containing all the methods to implement the DSATUR graph coloring algorithm
ColoringRLF
Class handling all the methods to implement the RLF graph coloring Algorithm.

The algorithm was based on this
ColoringUtilities
Class handling Coloring algorithms, mostly consists of static methods
ColoringWelshPowell
Class handling the Welsh and Powell algorithm
Coordinate
This class extends GeoPosition, from JxMapViewer, but takes care of the direction char ('N', 'E'...) that are stored in the source File.
FIGImportation
This class contains all the functions/procedures linked to FIG importation.
Flight
Flight extends SingleNode, from GraphStream, and is a node of a FlightsIntersectionGraph.
FlightFactory
Class handling the creation of Flight objects through the addNode method of graphstream
FlightsIntersectionGraph
The FlightIntersectionGraph (aka.
FlightWaypoint
This class is the MapWaypoint which is used to represent Flights on the Map.
GraphSAE
Abstract class containing our default graph attributes
InactiveAirportWaypoint
This class is a Waypoint on the Map which represents an inactive Airport.
InvalidCoordinateException
This exception is threw when an invalid format of Coordinate is found in a source File
InvalidEntryException
Exception threw when a wrong value is passed in a mehod.
InvalidFileFormatException
Threw if the File which is currently read contains a format error.
InvalidTimeException
Error managing a wrong time frame being entered in a FlightTime object
Map
This class is the Map which appears on the Application.
MapWaypoint
This class puts interactive Waypoints on the Application's map.
MapWaypointButton
This class is the button of a MapWaypoint, and allows the user to click and interact with the MapWaypoints on the Map.
MapWaypointPainter
This class paints the different Waypoints on a Map object.
NComboBoxGraph
This class create custom ComboBox for Graph Menu with a Default renderer
NComboBoxTime
This class is for create a custom JComboxBox Is a default one --> Time for Map
NDefaultRenderer<T>
The default renderer for the Combo boxes of this app.
NFileChooser
The customized file chooser, with all the correct filters, etc...
NFilledButton
A nice button, filled in black, with text written in white
NFlightTableInfoModel
Model for JTable The table's columns are defined by the enum Titles and the values contained will depend on the Airport's FlightList
NFlightTableInfoModel.Titles
Enum containing for each column its title and type
NFlightTableRenderer
Renderer used for the flight table shown when AirportWaypoints are clicked
NGraphInfoPanel
Class which create a panel of INFORMATION GRAPH The panel is situe in right bottom to the frame
NGraphMenuPanel
Class which create a JPanel of MENU for the graph Change parameter of the graph Location : Left to the Frame
NGraphNotHerePanel
Placeholder panel for when the graph has been moved to another frame
NImportButtonPanel
Creates a JPanel of importation for Flights and Airport
NImportFileButton
The default button for importation panel.
NImportScreen
This class create a panel for App's information and importation of necesseray files It's the first panel you see when you open the App
NInfoPanel
The JPanel that is prompted when a MapWaypoint is pressed, showing all the required informations
NMainScreen
This class creates the amin panel of the App where you can see the map and the graph of choosen files The class is one of the two Panel ADD directely in the JFrame (App)
NMapCheckBox
Default CheckBox style for MAP MENU
NMapMenuPanel
Creates a panel Menu for Map Help the user to modified appareance of the Map with JChekBox 1) See lines for Flight 2) See icon of used airport 3) See icon of not used airport 4) See icon of flight, the localization depends of the time GirdLayout: LINE : 5 COLUMN : 1 HGap : 0 VGap : 15
NMaxGraphFrame
Create a Panel for MaxGraph, it's a frame for seeing the graph bigger (with informations)
NMinGraphPanel
This class creates a Panel for see the graph There is also a expand button to see the graph in a other JFrame (it's bigger) (nice)
NSkullPanel
Panel shown if no graph has been imported, it contains a SINGLE GIANT SKULL IMAGE (or a placeholder text if you dare delete it)
NSliderTime
Slider situe in te center of the Body of the App The slider give the user access to change simulation time If the user push the button right to the Slider The simulation go and the slider move
NTime
Class handling hours and minutes only for easier access and manipulation in the Flight class
NTimeComboBoxRenderer
Class of renderer for Time ComboBoxs Add a 0 before 0 to 9 number
NTimePanel
A time Panel for JcomboxBoxs (hour/min) + the Slider (time) + PLAY button (simulation) ActionListener for the simulation here
ObjectNotFoundException
This exception was meant to be thrown when the object searched by the method getAttribute(key : String) returns "null".
PanelCreator
Class handling the rendering of Graphs and the events on its panel
RotatedImage
A RotatedImage is an Image which is rotated from a radian value, passed in parameter
TestGraph
TestGraph is the basic class to handle the "graph-testX.txt" files.
TestGraphImportation
This class contains all the functions/procedures linked to TestGraph importation.
